The issue here is that you are trying to output the entire object directly, which is being converted to the string "[object Object]". 
You should access the individual probabilities from the returned hashmap and choose the maximum probability outcome. Let me provide you with an updated function to handle this.
```javascript
function PredictCirrhosisOutcomes(N_Days, Drug, Age, Sex, Ascites, Hepatomegaly, Spiders, Edema, Bilirubin, Cholesterol, Albumin, Copper, Alk_Phos, SGOT, Tryglicerides, Platelets, Prothrombin, Stage) {
  // Your prediction code here
  // Calculate probabilities for each outcome (C, CL, D)
  // Return hashmap with probabilities
  const probabilities = {
    C: 0.5,
    CL: 0.3,
    D: 0.2
  };

  // Find the outcome with the maximum probability
  let maxOutcome = "";
  let maxProbability = 0;
  for (const outcome in probabilities) {
    if (probabilities[outcome] > maxProbability) {
      maxOutcome = outcome;
      maxProbability = probabilities[outcome];
    }
  }

  return maxOutcome;
}
```
Now, when you call the function with the input you provided, it will return the outcome with the highest probability (either "C", "CL", or "D").
